{
  "stem": "4284.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he yelled and screamed at me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he kicked me out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you-- there were two or three steps that I fell down because I got a major, major kick.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was no way to control it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But surprisingly enough, the loaf of bread and one tomato followed-- the only kind I ever received in all these years.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I went to make my report, which I had the papers there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because he realized I had a, a mission.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was the day, which was the most horrible that one could think of, where the trucks of the night's previous night's selection-- was waiting to go to Birkenau to be exterminated.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I had to walk between those two.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now here I was bloody.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I had a loaf of bread under my arm, which I was hiding under my uniform, making me probably look a little bit less emaciated, squeezing and holding on to the tomato.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And nobody, strangely enough, even questioned me whether I, I do not belong on either one of these trucks.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that was probably the most horrifying moment of pure innocence, you know, where your life was threatened by the circumstances in which you found yourself.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We stayed there for quite some time, for, well, a long time, doing the work, not having any idea-- by now, it's 1944-- that anything had been invaded.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We had no idea that there was anything politically, militarily.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Nobody has absolutely no knowledge.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "A few rumors here and there, but your rumors are mostly about survival.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were put with 20 other youngsters into a neighboring camp called Plawy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "This was in January of-- no, this was October, 1944-- yeah, October, '44.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
